hands_on_practices.problem:
In a simplified model of a cellular signaling pathway, the interactions between six proteins, labeled P1, P2, P3, P4, P5, and P6, are studied. An interaction consists of one protein activating another, creating a directed link of influence. The observed activating interactions are as follows:

- P1 activates P2.
- P2 activates P3.
- P3 activates P1, P4, and P6.
- P4 activates P5.
- P5 activates P4.

There are no other activating interactions among this set of proteins. A protein is considered to be part of a feedback loop if there exists a directed path of influence, involving one or more steps, that starts at the protein and eventually returns to it.

Which of the following sets contains all proteins, and only those proteins, that are part of at least one feedback loop in this signaling network?

A. {P1, P2, P3}

B. {P4, P5}

C. {P1, P2, P3, P4, P5}

D. {P1, P2, P3, P4, P5, P6}

E. {P3, P4, P6}
